OL,7,FHe, who has broken China's marathon
OL,8,Frecord twice in the past two years,
OL,9,Fwas rewarded with $5,500 (#4,400) for
OL,10,Ffinishing first place.
OL,12,FHe is ranked 77th in the world in
OL,13,Fmen's marathon by World Athletics and
OL,14,Fis expected to lead the way for Asian
OL,15,Frunners in the upcoming Summer
OL,16,FOlympics in Paris.
